<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1175">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">von Holleben</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial German Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-20"><hi rend="italic">July 20,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to
                            acknowledge your excellency’s favor of the 15th instant relative to the
                            entrance of neutral warships into, and their departure from, a blockaded
                            port, and to state that I have informed my Government of its
                            contents.</p>
                        <p>I avail myself of this occasion to renew to you, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Holleben.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>